net.opentsdb.query.expression

Class TimeSyncedIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.query.expression.TimeSyncedIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITimeSyncedIterator

    public class TimeSyncedIterator
extends Object
implements ITimeSyncedIterator
    Holds the results of a sub query (a single metric) and iterates over each resultant series in lock-step for expression evaluation.
    Since:
    2.3

      • TimeSyncedIterator

        public TimeSyncedIterator(String id,
                          ByteSet query_tagks,
                          DataPoints[] dps)
        Instantiates an iterator based on the results of a TSSubQuery. This will setup the emitters so it's safe to call values()
        Parameters:
        id - The name of the query.
        query_tagks - The set of tags used in filters on the query.
        dps - The data points fetched from storage.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if one of the parameters is null or the ID is empty

        public ITimeSyncedIterator getCopy()
